PARIS New Zealand fly-half Beauden Barrett is in line for a third successive world best player award after being nominated in a short-list of five by World Rugby on Friday.Fellow All Black and winger Rieko Ioane, South African duo Malcolm Marx (hooker) and Faf De Klerk (scrum-half) and Irish fly-half Johnny Sexton make up the nominations.Barrett, 27 and with 70 caps, scored seven tries this season including four against the Wallabies in a 40-12 win in August.  